The paper proposes a method for generating adversarial examples using a GAN, which is a popular technique in the fields of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of projected gradient descent (PGD) attack, which is a common technique in adversarial attacks, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible sub-categories.
